01847 /* OpenSolaris 2008.11 and 2009.06 keyboard layouts
01848  *
01849  * While OpenSolaris comes with Xorg and XKB, it maintains a set of keyboard layout
01850  * names that map directly to a particular keyboard layout in XKB. Fortunately for us,
01851  * this way of doing things comes from Solaris, which is XKB unaware. The same keyboard
01852  * layout naming system is used in Solaris, so we can use the same XKB configuration as
01853  * we would on OpenSolaris and get an accurate keyboard layout detection :)
01854  *
01855  * We can check for the current keyboard layout using the "kbd -l" command:
01856  *
01857  * type=6
01858  * layout=33 (0x21)
01859  * delay(ms)=500
01860  * rate(ms)=40
01861  *
01862  * We can check at runtime if the kbd utility is present, parse the output, and use the
01863  * keyboard layout indicated by the index given (in this case, 33, or US-English).
01864  */
01865
